\begin_layout Standard
The combination of uniform-variables provides a triangular distribution.
 Thus high combined scores - including both skills and raw-talent - are
 not uniformly distributed in the population even though raw-talent and
 skills may be distributed uniformly.
 An important result we used is that of PDF of a sum of uniformly distributed
 random variables 
\begin_inset Formula $z=ax+by$
\end_inset

 being the following convolution 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
f(z) & =\begin{cases}
\frac{z}{ab} & 0<z<a\\
\frac{1}{b} & a<z<b\\
\frac{a+b-z}{ab} & b<z<a+b\\
0 & otherwise
\end{cases}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The CDF corresponding to the above density is
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
F(z) & =\begin{cases}
\frac{z^{2}}{2ab} & 0<z<a\\
\frac{z-a/2}{b} & a<z<b\\
\frac{b-a/2}{b}+\frac{(a+b)z-z^{2}/2-(ab+b^{2}/2)}{ab} & b<z<a+b
\end{cases}\label{eq:triangular_pdf}
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

